Book Title: East of the Sun and West of the Moon: Old Tales from the North

Book Author: Peter Christen Asbjørnsen

Paragraph: (1) Once upon a time, a brave soldier discovered an old man who needed help. (2) After helping him, the soldier let him go. (3) The next day, the soldier's friends, a captain and a lieutenant, came back and were surprised to see the soldier safe. (4) The soldier shared his whole adventure with them and told them about some princesses who needed to be rescued. (5) Excited to help, the captain, the lieutenant, and the soldier prepared for their journey. (6) They packed a big basket, grabbed lots of rope, and headed to a mysterious mound.

 (7) At the mound, they followed the old man's instructions and dug up the ground until they found a huge stone slab. (8) It was so heavy that all three had to work together to move it. (9) After removing the slab, they saw a deep hole and tried to measure it with their ropes. (10) They attached the ropes together until they finally reached the bottom.

 (11) The captain decided to go down first. (12) He told his friends, "Pull me up quickly if I tug on the rope!". (13) Descending into the darkness, he felt scared when cold water sprayed over him. (14) He tugged the rope, and his friends quickly pulled him up.

 (15) Next, the lieutenant tried his luck, but he too got scared by a fire below and came back up.

 (16) Then it was the soldier's turn. (17) He bravely went down through the fire and water until he reached the bottom. (18) It was so dark, he could barely see anything. (19) Holding tightly to the basket, he walked around until he saw a faint light in the distance. (20) He followed the light, and soon everything around him started to brighten.

 (21) As he walked further, he saw the sun rising and the world transforming into a place as lovely as a fairy tale. (22) He walked past some shiny, fat cattle and reached a grand palace. (23) Inside the palace, he wandered through many rooms without seeing anyone.

 (24) Finally, he heard the sound of a spinning wheel. (25) He followed the sound and found the oldest princess spinning copper yarn in a room full of copper. (26) The princess looked up, surprised, and said, "Oh, dear! (27) What are Christian people doing here? (28) Heaven preserve you! (29) What do you want?". (30) The soldier smiled and knew his adventure was just beginning.



