Paragraph: (1) Richard Dalloway was staring at a shiny silver mug with two handles. (2) Nearby, Hugh Whitbread was looking at a fancy Spanish necklace. (3) He thought maybe Evelyn would like it. (4) Richard felt really slow and couldn't decide what to do. (5) He just watched. (6) Evelyn might want to buy the necklace. (7) Richard yawned. (8) He really wasn't interested, but Hugh was about to enter the shop.

 (9) "Okay, let's go," Richard said, following Hugh inside.

 (10) Richard didn't really want to go shopping for necklaces with Hugh. (11) But sometimes, you just end up doing things. (12) Hugh was talking about getting the necklace for Evelyn. (13) Richard thought about how silly it all seemed, buying necklaces for someone.

 (14) If Richard had a son, he would tell him to work hard. (15) But he had his daughter, Elizabeth, and he loved her so much.

 (16) Inside the shop, Hugh talked to the shopkeeper. (17) He wanted to know if Mr. Dubonnet was there. (18) Mr. Dubonnet knew exactly what jewelry Evelyn liked. (19) Richard found this all very strange. (20) Richard thought about his wife, Clarissa. (21) He hadn't given her a gift in a long time. (22) He remembered giving her a bracelet that she never wore. (23) That made him a bit sad. (24) He wanted to find her the perfect gift. (25) Hugh was talking loudly and didn't want to buy anything unless Mr. Dubonnet was there. (26) The young shop assistant looked embarrassed. (27) Richard couldn't believe how rude Hugh was acting. (28) He couldn't spend much more time with him. (29) Tipping his hat, Richard decided to leave. (30) He really wanted to see Clarissa and give her a special gift. (31) He felt a strong connection to her and was eager to see her again.



